(CNN)A climber was missing and two others were injured after a rockfall and avalanche on Mount Meeker in Colorado's Rocky Mountain National Park on Sunday morning, park authorities said in a news release. One of the male climbers was rescued by Rocky Mountain National Park Search and Rescue team members with the help of the Colorado National Guard, the release said. The man was flown to the Medical Center of the Rockies by medivac where he is being treated. A female climber had minor injuries, according to the release. Authorities continued to search for the third climber who was missing in the area where the avalanche happened, according to the release. Other area climbers witnessed the rockfall and the avalanche, park authorities said in the release. So far this year, 16 people have died in avalanches in the United States -- significantly below the 37 people who died last year, according to the Colorado Avalanche Information Center. 